What normalize-space() Does

normalize-space():
Removes leading spaces
Removes trailing spaces
Converts multiple spaces to a single space

Useful for text that has irregular spacing.

⭐ Correct Ways to Use It
✅ 1. Match element text exactly (common usage)
//div[normalize-space() = 'Login']


This finds:
<div>   Login   </div>
or
<div>Login</div>
or
<div>   Login Page    </div>  <!-- WRONG: if exact match needed -->

✅ 2. Contains text, ignoring extra spaces
//div[contains(normalize-space(), 'Login')]

Matches:
"Login"

" Login Page "

"Login Successful"

✅ 3. Based on an attribute
//div[@class='button' and normalize-space(text()) = 'Submit']

✅ 4. Use with text() explicitly
//div[normalize-space(text()) = 'Start Now']

⭐ Common Patterns
Find button by text:
//button[normalize-space()='Submit']

Find any element ignoring extra spaces:
//*[normalize-space()='Continue']

Find <span> containing text:
//span[contains(normalize-space(),'Profile')]



nested:
//span[normalize-space()='Samsung']

//direct--- only will target one span
//span[normalize-space(text())='Samsung']